WEBVTT

00:00.200 --> 00:03.945
<Font color=#FFFF00>When the Bough Breaks</font>

00:03.968 --> 00:06.100
♪ Yeah

00:06.133 --> 00:08.501
♪ Ooh

00:08.534 --> 00:10.634
♪ My temperature's a-risin'

00:10.667 --> 00:12.901
♪ I can feel
the fever's burning up ♪

00:12.934 --> 00:13.968
(Buzzes)

00:14.000 --> 00:15.968
♪ ooh
♪ hot, hot, hot

00:16.000 --> 00:16.968
(Buzz)

00:17.000 --> 00:18.467
♪ My temperature's a-risin'

00:18.701 --> 00:20.934
(Buzzing)
Yes. Yep. I'm coming.

00:21.434 --> 00:22.734
♪ temperature's a-risin'

00:23.367 --> 00:25.267
♪ I can feel
the fever's burning up ♪

00:25.301 --> 00:26.567
You are not going
to believe this.

00:26.668 --> 00:27.268
Paula.

00:27.269 --> 00:29.169
You are so not going
to believe this.

00:29.233 --> 00:29.934
What are you doing here?

00:30.034 --> 00:31.767
- I can't even believe it.
- Believe what?

00:31.801 --> 00:32.600
I can't tell you.

00:32.801 --> 00:34.501
I'm still asleep, aren't I?
I'm dreaming.

00:34.534 --> 00:36.701
I'm having a dream where
my book agent has shown up

00:36.702 --> 00:40.102
At my house at 7:00 A.M.
to not tell me something.

00:40.634 --> 00:41.167
Okay.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.701
It's not official yet,

00:43.734 --> 00:45.700
But... you, my dear,

00:46.400 --> 00:48.067
are at the top of their list,

00:48.668 --> 00:50.467
and I can't give you
any more details than that.

00:50.667 --> 00:51.768
You want some coffee?

00:51.801 --> 00:53.900
I'd love to sit down
and not discuss this further.

00:53.901 --> 00:54.901
I will tell you this--

00:55.334 --> 00:57.334
It's a major relaunch
of a major franchise--

00:57.467 --> 01:00.733
A 3-Book deal--
And they want you.

01:01.267 --> 01:02.533
"Heat Wave" comes out
in less than a week.

01:03.134 --> 01:05.367
The book party, which you
arranged, is Monday night.

01:05.734 --> 01:07.201
I'm trying to launch
my own character.

01:07.234 --> 01:08.701
Why would I want to get involved
with somebody else's?

01:08.767 --> 01:10.834
What if I told you
the character in question

01:11.034 --> 01:14.200
is a certain British
Secret Agent?

01:15.234 --> 01:16.167
You mean it's gonna be--

01:16.268 --> 01:18.568
Shh. Don't say it.
You'll jinx it.

01:18.833 --> 01:20.034
He's the reason
I became a writer.
(Cell phone ringing)

01:20.300 --> 01:20.733
I know.

01:20.734 --> 01:22.434
I mean,
he's the coolest spy ever.

01:22.467 --> 01:23.300
- Right.
- He's got gadgets,

01:23.301 --> 01:24.701
he's got babes, he's--

01:24.733 --> 01:26.967
And a payday
that is unbelievable.

01:26.968 --> 01:28.268
And they want me
for three new books?

01:28.300 --> 01:29.233
(Ringing continues)
Yes, now are you gonna get that?

01:29.301 --> 01:31.234
Because an unanswered phone
gives me agita.

01:32.535 --> 01:33.335
It's Beckett.

01:34.134 --> 01:35.433
(Ring)
A body must have dropped.

01:35.601 --> 01:36.868
Uh...

01:38.567 --> 01:39.401
I'll call her back.

01:39.700 --> 01:41.134
What other details can't you tell me?
(Chuckles)

01:42.534 --> 01:45.233
(Siren whoops)
Morning, gentlemen.

01:46.367 --> 01:47.200
So what do you got for us?

01:47.500 --> 01:49.301
Caucasian female, early 30s,

01:49.634 --> 01:51.301
No purse or I.D.
found on the body.

01:51.334 --> 01:52.300
Where is she?

01:53.833 --> 01:54.767
City workers found her

01:54.800 --> 01:56.601
When they opened the manhole
to check the line.

01:56.934 --> 01:57.501
(Police radio chatter)

02:04.700 --> 02:06.133
Something tells me
she didn't trip.

02:08.000 --> 02:10.234
Cause of death appears to be
blunt force trauma.

02:10.967 --> 02:13.134
She took a nasty blow
to the back of the head.

02:13.367 --> 02:16.034
But we found traces of blood spatter
over there on the sidewalk.

02:16.233 --> 02:17.701
Well, then it couldn't
have been a robbery.

02:17.901 --> 02:19.767
A mugger wouldn't bother
dragging her body that far

02:19.768 --> 02:20.468
just to hide it.

02:20.568 --> 02:22.434
Given the amount of decomposition,

02:23.101 --> 02:24.734
I'd say she was killed
about two days ago.

02:24.767 --> 02:26.601
Any chance you could
narrow that down for us?

02:26.634 --> 02:28.400
Any chance I can get her
to the lab first?

02:30.034 --> 02:31.300
I should be able to get you
a tighter window,

02:31.334 --> 02:33.300
maybe down to six or seven hours.

02:33.601 --> 02:34.901
All right, thank you.

02:36.167 --> 02:37.101
(Ryan)
Ah, good morning.

02:37.767 --> 02:39.234
Look who decided
to grace us with his presence.

02:40.067 --> 02:41.933
Did you have something
more important to do, Castle?

02:41.934 --> 02:43.034
I got held up at home.

02:43.234 --> 02:44.100
Was that the body?

02:44.201 --> 02:45.401
Yeah, it's on its way
to the morgue.

02:45.467 --> 02:47.168
- Aw.
- What, you wanted us to wait?

02:48.168 --> 02:50.601
Yeah, it's too bad, too.
It's your kinda case, bro.

02:50.902 --> 02:51.502
Yeah?

02:51.534 --> 02:55.167
Yeah, body was found down that
manhole over there, half eaten.

02:55.368 --> 02:56.168
Eaten?

02:56.169 --> 02:57.869
Yeah, it was covered
in some kind of green slime.

02:58.334 --> 03:00.167
- Whoa.
- Yeah, it was creepy.

03:00.601 --> 03:02.801
It's as if someone
or something is down there.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.767
Ah, that's--Okay,
very funny. That's great.

03:07.000 --> 03:08.001
Was there a body
down the manhole?

03:08.202 --> 03:10.102
- Yeah.
- Okay. Thank you. An adult.

03:10.467 --> 03:11.734
Yeah, you shoulda seen
what else was down there.

03:12.033 --> 03:14.233
Two metal canisters
with biohazard stickers

03:14.268 --> 03:15.600
and yellow powder inside of it.

03:15.601 --> 03:16.701
You opened the...

03:18.034 --> 03:19.434
All right. Tha--will someone
please tell me

03:19.467 --> 03:20.668
what's really going on here?

03:20.869 --> 03:22.469
We're gonna check nearby trash
cans for the murder weapon.

03:22.768 --> 03:24.500
Uh, what was the murder weapon,
by the way?

03:24.501 --> 03:25.701
Some kind of death ray.

03:25.800 --> 03:27.167
Turns your insides out.

03:30.568 --> 03:32.068
(Perlmutter) Her fingerprints
came back negative.

03:32.069 --> 03:33.169
(Camera beeps, shutter clicks)

03:33.170 --> 03:35.470
Missing persons didn't have
anyone matching her description.

03:36.500 --> 03:37.334
(Camera shutter clicks)

03:38.035 --> 03:39.835
Your boys didn't happen to find
her purse by any chance?

03:40.201 --> 03:42.267
No, no purse,
no murder weapon.

03:42.368 --> 03:44.267
Then we have ourselves
a Jane Doe.

03:44.934 --> 03:47.634
Two days and no one steps
forward to say she's missing.

03:47.933 --> 03:49.300
Which means she probably
lived alone

03:49.434 --> 03:52.067
and she didn't have a job
where she needed to be.

03:52.200 --> 03:53.668
I can tell you this much--
She's an immigrant,

03:53.767 --> 03:55.301
Probably from Eastern Europe.

03:55.402 --> 03:56.102
Her dental work?

03:56.103 --> 03:58.203
Yeah, she's got a couple
of stainless steel crowns.

03:58.401 --> 03:59.733
We don't use 'em anymore
in the states,

03:59.734 --> 04:02.034
But they're still common
in the former Soviet Block.

04:02.634 --> 04:05.733
Uh, we found this scrunched in
the bottom of her pants pocket.

04:06.034 --> 04:06.834
Candy wrapper.

04:07.701 --> 04:09.334
It's got some kind of writing on it.

04:09.401 --> 04:11.400
The lettering has
diacritical marks on it.

04:12.001 --> 04:14.001
They're accent marks
used to represent sounds

04:14.034 --> 04:14.767
That are alien to latin.

04:14.834 --> 04:18.034
I'm gonna go with
Slavic Cyrillic. No, Czech.

04:18.567 --> 04:19.500
And you know this how?

04:19.701 --> 04:21.401
I almost ordered
a Russian bride once.

04:22.000 --> 04:23.600
You know, a Czech mate?

04:25.067 --> 04:25.833
I'm gonna run this down.

04:25.867 --> 04:27.100
There can't be
too many shops in the area

04:27.167 --> 04:28.134
That sell this stuff.

04:31.035 --> 04:31.735
Hey, Perlmutter.

04:32.100 --> 04:33.467
I'm having a book launch party
Monday night. You wanna come?

04:34.068 --> 04:34.868
Please.

04:35.267 --> 04:36.200
I'll put you down as a maybe.

04:40.033 --> 04:41.301
(Castle) This is gonna
weird you out a little bit,

04:41.400 --> 04:43.167
But check this out.
I mean, it just seems like...

04:43.401 --> 04:45.567
It seems to bend
the space time continuum.

04:45.601 --> 04:47.200
Look, just when you think
there can't be another one.

04:48.201 --> 04:48.201
Wow
What is he doing?

04:48.234 --> 04:49.767
We hit about a dozen little shops

04:49.834 --> 04:51.300
Trying to find
that candy wrapper.
(Castle speaks indistinctly)

04:51.367 --> 04:54.534
And he insisted on
buying something in every shop.

04:55.035 --> 04:56.535
(laughs)
In every shop?

04:57.033 --> 04:58.100
No wrapper, though.

04:58.101 --> 04:59.601
Something tells me,
if he decides to put

04:59.634 --> 05:01.134
the great candy wrapper hunt
in his next book,

05:01.167 --> 05:02.367
He'll give it a happier ending.

05:02.568 --> 05:05.768
Wait, sir. Sir, uh, next book?

05:07.100 --> 05:08.400
Is he writing
another Nikki Heat novel?

05:08.434 --> 05:09.434
The deal was for one book.

05:09.935 --> 05:11.435
- I assumed that--
- You were off the hook?

05:11.734 --> 05:13.200
You know how the Mayor feels
about Castle.

05:13.234 --> 05:14.734
<i>If the man is gonna write
another book about you--</i>

05:14.735 --> 05:17.135
I am not Nikki Heat, sir.

05:18.600 --> 05:21.200
Yeah. Well, uh, hizzoner expects
your cooperation either way.

05:23.400 --> 05:24.868
(Elevator bell dings)

05:24.901 --> 05:26.733
(Ryan)
Yo! Found your candy.

05:27.000 --> 05:28.601
You found it?
Get outta town.

05:28.867 --> 05:31.234
- Little grocery on 47th and 9th.
- Yep.

05:31.867 --> 05:33.301
I told you we shoulda
checked the West End.

05:33.802 --> 05:35.302
(Ryan) Owner recognized
our vic's picture.

05:35.801 --> 05:37.534
Said she'd come by
every couple of weeks

05:37.535 --> 05:38.935
and stock up on stuff
from back home.

05:38.936 --> 05:39.736
(Castle)
Hmm.

05:39.934 --> 05:42.433
Kinda tastes like soap.
I like it.

05:43.567 --> 05:44.501
Did he give you a name?

05:44.602 --> 05:45.502
(Esposito)
No, but he did point us

05:45.533 --> 05:46.667
To where
he thought she might live.

05:46.834 --> 05:48.168
Apparently there's an S.R.O.
Not far from

05:48.169 --> 05:50.569
where we found the body
that caters to Czech illegals.

05:51.033 --> 05:52.401
Well, then let's pay it
a visit.

05:54.234 --> 05:57.400
Yeah, I know her.
The lady in 5-C--Eliska Sokol.

05:58.267 --> 05:59.234
She was a nice person.

06:00.001 --> 06:01.300
She kept to herself, but nice.

06:02.334 --> 06:04.101
Yeah, why anybody'd
want to kill her...

06:04.467 --> 06:05.600
How long did she live
in the building?

06:05.867 --> 06:06.667
About six months.

06:06.968 --> 06:08.368
Never gave you any trouble?

06:08.567 --> 06:10.500
No. I wish all my tenants
were like her.

06:10.501 --> 06:12.534
She paid her rent on time
every week in cash.

06:13.600 --> 06:15.534
- You said 5-C?
- Yeah, you want to see it?

06:15.668 --> 06:18.001
Yeah, please. Why don't you guys
start knocking on doors,

06:18.002 --> 06:20.102
and  see if any of the other
tenants can shed some light.

06:20.234 --> 06:20.701
Right on.

06:25.067 --> 06:25.734
Here it is.

06:25.901 --> 06:27.034
Let me know when you're done.

06:27.068 --> 06:28.033
Thanks.

06:31.200 --> 06:31.967
From what I'm seeing,

06:31.968 --> 06:33.768
it's a pretty good bet
she lived alone.

06:33.833 --> 06:35.601
There's not even
a telephone.

06:39.434 --> 06:41.901
Something tells me
she didn't have many visitors.

06:42.834 --> 06:43.667
Hey.

06:45.334 --> 06:47.400
Work calendar maybe?
Keeping track of shifts.

06:47.634 --> 06:49.501
There's nothing
past last Wednesday.

06:51.433 --> 06:52.434
Postcards from home.

07:00.434 --> 07:01.867
Hmm.

07:03.000 --> 07:09.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:10.033 --> 07:11.668
If a picture's worth
a thousand words,

07:12.367 --> 07:14.100
This one says "not a fan."

07:14.467 --> 07:15.967
The scratches
go through the paper.

07:17.967 --> 07:20.167
Whoever she is, looks like
our vic hated her.

07:20.701 --> 07:22.167
Could be the feeling
was mutual.

